      "notes": [
        {
          "text": "The three tiers (Reader, Orchestrator, Executor) each operate with different trust levels and tool access. The key insight: a tier that cannot reach external systems cannot exfiltrate data, even if compromised.",
          "pageNo": 6,
          "type": "notes",
          "parentID": "peer-book-001",
          "id": "pn-01",
          "createdAt": 1778401500000,
          "updatedAt": 1778401500000
        },
        {
          "text": "Deny-by-default means every tool call must be explicitly whitelisted. This flips the traditional approach: instead of blocking known bad actions, you only allow known good ones.",
          "pageNo": 7,
          "type": "notes",
          "parentID": "peer-book-001",
          "id": "pn-02",
          "createdAt": 1778401900000,
          "updatedAt": 1778401900000
        },
        {
          "text": "MCP connectors as the data layer — one connector, many agents. The access boundary IS the security boundary.",
          "pageNo": 8,
          "type": "notes",
          "parentID": "peer-book-001",
          "id": "pn-03",
          "createdAt": 1778402100000,
          "updatedAt": 1778402100000
        }
      ],
